headline: $65.9 Million Net-Leased Portfolio 70 DST Fully Subscribed, Strengthening ExchangeRight's Essential Income REIT Pipeline

headline: 3 Reasons DLTR is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Dollar Tree’s 32.6% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 19.5%, and its stock price has climbed to $131.25 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
